It would also be good to remove `qa/pull-tester/tests_config.py` from .gitignore, but that will cause it to appear as an untracked file in git status for anyone who builds on a previous commit and then git pulls.
@jnewbery, yea, that's why I just left it for now.
Makes sense, this could be done a week or so after the release of 0.14.0, when developers no longer jump back and forth so often between branches.
